##################################
# shared by frontend and backend #
##################################
# SMS_VERSION
#     A variable that allows to show the current version of the SMS.
#     It is usually filled within the CI pipeline steps and represents either the current commit (staging) or the tag (production).
# SMS_BACKEND_URL
#     The url to access the backend.
# NUXT_ENV_CLIENT_ID
#     Client id for the open id connect configuration.
#     The frontend needs to have it in order to allow the login in the application. The backend needs it as the swagger ui page also allows the users to login.
# ALLOWED_MIME_TYPES
#     A list of mimetypes that are allowed for uploaded files. We restrict it in order
#     to avoid misuse of the upload function.
#     Documents are usually allowed, but no
#     large data files.
# NUXT_ENV_SCOPE
#     Same as the NUXT_ENV_CLIENT_ID this one is shared also for the backend to allow login on the swagger ui page.
# INSTITUTE
#     The institute is used to link to the institute specific pages for imprint, data protection etc. Can be `fzj`, `gfz`, `kit` or `ufz`.

